s:1304:"<p>This course introduces you to the core building blocks of the web—<strong>HTML (HyperText Markup Language)</strong>. Designed for absolute beginners, this section focuses on understanding the structure and syntax of HTML and how to use tags to create web pages. You will learn how to define headings, paragraphs, lists, links, images, and how to organize content using semantic HTML elements. By the end of this course, you’ll have the foundational skills to build static websites and prepare for styling them with CSS.<br /><br /></p>
<p>This section includes:</p>
<p></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>🎥 <strong>Class Video</strong> – A guided walkthrough of HTML concepts and examples</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>📝 <strong>Class Note</strong> – A downloadable summary of key topics and syntax</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>🔗 <strong>Additional Reference Materials</strong> – Links to trusted learning resources for deeper exploration</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>📋 <strong>Assignment</strong> – A practical task to apply what you’ve learned</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>❓ <strong>Quiz</strong> – A short test to check your understanding and reinforce learning</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><br />Use all the resources provided to get hands-on experience and build confidence in creating your own web pages with HTML.</p>";